===Etymology===
From French [[taximètre]] < German [[Taxameter]], coined from Medieval Latin [[taxa]] (tax, charge) < Proto-Indo-European base '''*tag-''' (to touch, to handle).

===Noun===
'''taximeter'''
# a [[device]] installed in a [[taxicab]] that [[calculate]]s the [[fare]] based upon [[distance]] [[travelled]] and [[waiting]] [[time]].

